description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you interested in promoting good musculoskeletal health?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you able to undertake assessments, offer recommendations and early interventions to support staff suffering with musculoskeletal disorders that are affecting their work?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Would you like to be part of the team coordinating the trust wide moving and handling training programs across all of Kettering Hospital staff groups?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If this is you we would love to hear from you !&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for someone to act as an adviser and trainer who is knowledgeable and skilful in all aspects of safe handling and musculoskeletal health to work as part of a team supporting a high quality comprehensive back care advisory service. We are proud of the service we currently offer supporting trust wide staff with musculoskeletal challenges to remain in the workplace whilst also ensuring our staff are safe at work and our patients receive good quality handling. We have on offer a part-time 30 hour post and we would love to discuss further with you if you’d like to know more.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Rozz Strachan&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Muscular Skeletal Advisor&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address rozz.strachan@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01536 492157&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sheila Turner Head of Education and Learning 01536 493772&lt;/p&gt;
